<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1619">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/130.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am informed by Mr. J. M. Hyatt that in the contract referred to in my
                            telegram of yesterday the provision for hypothecating the $250,000
                            annuity has been replaced by a provision for hypothecating a portion of
                            the $6,000,000 belonging to the Government of Panama in New York. Mr.
                            Hyatt also says that the substitution has been acquiesced in by the
                            Department of State.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>